text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia sibilans, commonly known as the Whispering myall, is a shrub or tree of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Mid West, Gascoyne, Pilbara and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The bushy shrub or tree typically grows to a height of 3 to 7.5 metres (10 to 25 ft) and produces yellow flowers.
